# Rule 04 — Frontend Standards

The frontend is a trust boundary and the surface where PHI is rendered to
humans. These rules apply to every UI component, page, and hook.

## Accessibility

- All components MUST meet **WCAG 2.1 AA**.
- Every interactive element MUST have a stable, meaningful name exposed to
  assistive technology.
- Color alone MUST NOT convey meaning; pair with text or iconography.
- Keyboard navigation MUST reach every interactive element in a logical
  order, with visible focus.
- Forms MUST expose errors programmatically, not only visually.
- Motion MUST respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## PHI rendering

- Components that render PHI MUST be explicitly tagged (e.g., a `data-phi`
  attribute or equivalent). Tagged components MUST NOT:
  - Be logged, screenshotted by analytics, or sent to session-replay tools.
  - Be persisted to `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, `IndexedDB`, or cookies.
  - Be copied to the clipboard without an explicit user action.
- Tooltips, toasts, and error banners MUST NOT include PHI from unexpected
  contexts.

## State management

- Client-side state is **not** an authorization boundary. Privilege checks
  MUST happen on the server for every sensitive action.
- Forms MUST validate using schemas from `packages/schemas/`. Client-only
  validation is permitted as UX sugar, never as the sole check.
- Derived state MUST be memoized deterministically; hidden mutations via
  refs on render paths are prohibited.

## Data fetching

- All server calls MUST go through `packages/api-client`. Inline `fetch`
  against internal services is prohibited.
- Loading, empty, error, and partial states MUST be explicit for every
  data-bound component. `undefined` rendered as "—" without intent is not
  acceptable.
- Requests MUST include a correlation / request ID propagated to the server
  for audit.

## Components

- Shared components live in `packages/ui/`. App-specific one-offs live
  beside their feature.
- Components MUST be typed, have a stable API surface, and have at least one
  test covering default, error, and empty states.
- `any` / `unknown` escape hatches REQUIRE a comment stating the constraint
  that forces them and a follow-up issue.

## Styling

- Design tokens from `packages/ui/` are the source of truth for color,
  spacing, and typography. Hard-coded values are prohibited in feature code.
- Dark mode and high-contrast mode MUST be supported at the token layer.
- No inline style strings containing PHI.

## Internationalization & locale

- All user-facing strings MUST be wired through the i18n layer.
- Dates, numbers, and units MUST be formatted via locale-aware helpers, not
  string concatenation. Clinical units (e.g., mmHg, kg, °C) are explicit.

## Performance

- Routes MUST be code-split. Bundle budgets are declared in
  `packages/config/` and enforced in CI.
- Images MUST be responsive and lazy-loaded unless above the fold.
- Third-party scripts REQUIRE an ADR and MUST be loaded with integrity and
  referrer controls.

## Analytics

- Only approved analytics events fire. Event names and payloads are declared
  in `packages/schemas/analytics/`.
- Analytics payloads MUST NOT contain PHI. A redaction audit is part of the
  PR checklist when analytics are touched.
